    <h1>Data and Account Deletion Request</h1>
    
    <p>At <strong>Plot Twist!</strong>, developed by <strong>Martin Del Gaudio (mgdworks)</strong>, we value your privacy and provide a clear path for you to manage your data. Below are the steps and information regarding the deletion of your account and associated data.</p>

    <h2>Steps to request account deletion</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
        <p>To request the deletion of your account, please follow these steps:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Send an email from the account associated with the app to: <a href="mailto:mgdelgaudio@gmail.com">mgdelgaudio@gmail.com</a></li>
            <li>Use the subject line: <strong>"Account Deletion Request - Plot Twist!"</strong></li>
            <li>Include your full name and the email address used to log in via Google OAuth.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Our team will process your request and confirm the deletion within <strong>7 business days</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What data will be deleted?</h2>
    <p>Upon completing the request, the following information will be permanently removed from our active databases:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Your user profile information (Name and Email retrieved via Google).</li>
        <li>Any personalized settings or preferences saved within the Application.</li>
        <li>Historical logs of AI-generated content associated with your unique ID.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What data might be retained?</h2>
    <p>We only retain data that is strictly necessary for legal or security purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Security Logs:</strong> Basic interaction logs are kept for a maximum period of 30 days to prevent fraud and ensure system stability before being automatically purged.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> If applicable, transaction records or legal notices will be kept for the period required by law.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Once the account is deleted, it cannot be recovered. If you wish to use the Application again, you will need to create a new account.</p>

